What is the step-by-step set of instructions used to solve a problem? = Algorithm
What program design tool uses symbols to represent processes and decisions visually? = Flowchart
What structured, code-like description of an algorithm uses informal language? = Pseudocode
What phase involves understanding the problem requirements first? = Analyze
What phase involves turning the plan into actual code? = Implement
What phase focuses on testing, debugging, and improving the program? = Maintenance
What type of code can computers directly understand in binary form? = Machine Code
What do humans write and read before translation into machine code? = Source Code
What translates the entire program into machine code at once? = Compiler
What translates code line-by-line during execution? = Interpreter
What term refers to information processed or stored by a program? = Data
What container stores a value in memory with a name? = Variable
What type of variable persists for the entire execution of a program? = Static
What type of variable is allocated during runtime? = Dynamic
What function displays output to the screen in Python? = print()
What type of string literal allows embedding expressions inside curly braces? = f-string
What statement reads input from the user? = input()
What symbol is used for assigning a value to a variable? = =
What data type represents whole numbers? = Integer
What data type represents decimal numbers? = Float
What function returns the number of characters in a string? = len()
What operator joins two strings together? = +
What character begins a comment in Python? = #
What documentation string is written using triple quotes? = Docstring
What automatic conversion between data types is done by Python itself? = Implicit type conversion
What manual conversion using functions like int() or float() is called? = Explicit type conversion
What operator performs floor division and returns the quotient only? = //
What operator returns the remainder after division? = %
What official Python style guide defines coding standards? = PEP 8
What loop is best used when the number of iterations is known? = For loop